    <h1>User Web Pages</h1>

    <p>This is the web server for Monash University users. All web pages will have a
URL in the form: <strong>https://users.monash.edu.au/~username</strong>
</p>

     <h2>Policies and Guidelines for Authors</h2>

<p>Use of Monash University's IT facilities is governed by the policy for
<a href="https://www.adm.monash.edu.au/unisec/pol/itec12.html">Acceptable Use of IT Facilities by Students</a>
and the
<a href="https://www.adm.monash.edu.au/unisec/pol/itec16.html">IT Use Policy</a>
for staff and other authorised users.
</p>

<p>For detailed policy on web pages, refer to 
<a href="https://www.adm.monash.edu.au/execserv/policies/Information-Technology-Policies/Information-Technology-use-Policy-Staff-and-Other-Authorised-Users.html">Information Technology Use Policy - Staff & Other Authorised Users</a>.
</p>

<!--- 
<p>All user content must not require access to, or special configuration
of the web server software. Users requiring this must use <a href="https://www.its.monash.edu.au/staff/systems/unix/"><strong>sng</strong></a>.</p>
-->

<p>Content which interferes with the performance of the service,
causes loss of data or service, attempts to damage hardware or software,
manipulate or damage files belonging to another user,
or to circumvent system security, will be removed.
Usage is <a href="usage/index.html">monitored</a> (Monash only);
<a href="usage2/index.html">SSL</a> (Monash only).</p>

    <p><strong>Caution:</strong> Unauthorized or improper use of this service
may result in administrative disciplinary action and
civil and criminal penalties.
Use of this service constitutes consent to security monitoring and testing.</p>

<!---

     <h2>Creating Your Website</h2>

     <p>Configure your account before adding your web content.</p>

     <ol>

     <li>Access your home folder.<br/>

    Connect to
<a href="https://www.its.monash.edu.au/staff/systems/unix/"><strong>sng</strong></a>
using <a href="http://www.its.monash.edu/staff/systems/linux/technical/linux-remoteaccess.html">SSH</a> before going on to the next step.</li>


     <li>Type <code>home.page.setup</code> at the prompt. It will automatically
     create a <strong>WWW</strong> folder (if you do not have one) and set the permissions so that everyone can
     view your website. Use <code>home.page.setup</code> again at any
     time to fix your website.</li>

     <li>Check the <a href="https://users.monash.edu.au/about/">web server software configuration</a> (Authcate restricted). </li>

     </ol>

     <p><strong>Hint:</strong> If <code>home.page.setup</code> is not in your path,
     use
     <code>/afs/monash/pack/cflabs/master/usr/local/etc/home_page_setup.sh</code>
     instead.

     <br><br>

